{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8406f646-d2bf-427f-b3b5-d2c23e613dcf","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. `&` → `/` for AND logic\nMTP uses `/` (not `&`) as the AND operator in `--filter`.\n\n### 2. `Category` trait → `Category` still works, but the property name matters\nWith MTP, trait-based filtering uses the syntax `Category=Smoke` (this part is the same), but `FullyQualifiedName` works as `FullyQualifiedName`.\n\n### Translated command\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe only change is `&` → `/`.\n\n### Quick reference of MTP filter operators\n\n| Operator | VSTest | MTP |\n|----------|--------|-----|\n| AND | `&` | `/` |\n| OR | `\\|` | `\\|` |\n| NOT | `!` | `!` |\n| Contains | `~` | `~` |\n| Equals | `=` | `=` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edd7978c-1a7a-48b7-8a46-2491ee2ba04f","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"7038:83273:E1F5251:F827A69:69F2A91B"},"id":"6031e8bc-76f3-444e-96c5-8dde7ba9d5b6","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:58:10.088Z","parentId":"d07ec500-b1bd-409d-9820-fee92479b1f1"}
